# Documentation Generation Guidelines

**Activation Mode:** Model Decision
**Description:** Apply when writing documentation, comments, README files, and technical specifications

## Documentation Standards
- Write clear, concise documentation with practical examples
- Use proper Markdown formatting and structure
- Include code examples that demonstrate usage
- Provide context and reasoning behind decisions
- Document platform-specific behavior when applicable (iOS vs Android differences)

## Code Comments
- Write self-documenting code with descriptive variable names
- Add comments for complex business logic
- Document function parameters and return types
- Explain the "why" not just the "what"
- Document React Native specific implementations

## README Files
- Include project overview and purpose
- Provide clear installation and setup instructions for both development environments
- Document available scripts and commands for React Native/Expo
- Include examples of common use cases
- Document platform-specific setup requirements

## API Documentation
- Document all public interfaces and methods
- Include request/response examples for mobile API calls
- Specify parameter types and constraints
- Document error cases and handling
- Include platform compatibility information

## Technical Specifications
- Define clear requirements and acceptance criteria
- Include architecture diagrams when helpful
- Document design decisions and trade-offs
- Maintain up-to-date documentation with code changes
- Document performance considerations for mobile devices